com.neu.prattle.model

Class Group

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.neu.prattle.model.Group

  • public class Group
extends java.lang.Object
    Group object which can be composed of an arbitrary number of Users. Groups can also have/be subgroups.

    jdwilson73

    • Field Detail

      • id

        private int id

      • isActive

        private boolean isActive
        Whether or not the group is still active. If Group is deactivated, no changes can be made to Group's fields. Additionally, Group will be invisible in all searches by Users who are not moderators of the Group. Also no messages may be routed to/from the deactivated Group. If Group was deactivated while serving as a sub/supergroup of another Group, that status will not be retained--i.e. the Group will have to re-merge manually.

      • moderators

        private java.util.Set<User> moderators
        Set of Users serving as moderators for this Group. Every Group must have at least one moderator.

      • groupName

        private java.lang.String groupName
        Current name of the Group (may change).

      • memberAliases

        private java.util.Map<User,java.lang.String> memberAliases
        Tracks the current alias of each User in the Group. An alias is the specific name used by a User in the given Group.

      • joinUserQueue
